correctness.rationale: Extensive factual and schema issues. Major process details are invented and not traceable to the article: ALD method (TALD), specific precursors/co-reactant (In–Ga bimetallic precursor, DEZn, O3), carrier/purge gases (Ar/N2), reactor manufacturer, deposition temperature (200 °C), pressure (0.1 mmHg), GPC, dosing/purge times, flow rates, supercycle design, and most material properties (refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap measurement, resistivity, carrier density with Hall method, uniformity, conformality, roughness, density, composition/atomic ratios) and on/off ratio. Only a few values are supported (substrate, 10 nm IGZO channel, device structure, μ_FE = 18.3 cm^2/V·s, V_TH = 1.1 V, SS = 67.8 mV/dec). Internal inconsistency: GPC = 0.1 Å with 100 cycles cannot yield 10 nm (requires ~1 Å/cycle). Schema violations: plasmaPower is null (should be omitted or a valid object), mis-nesting of properties (saturation, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates placed inside thicknessControl instead of processParameters), duplicate filmThickness fields (inside growthPerCycle and again at processParameters and inside thicknessControl), and an incoherent supercycleDesign listing 'InGaZnO' rather than separate In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO subcycles. Corrections needed: remove or mark unknown any unreported parameters; relocate fields per schema; omit plasmaPower for thermal ALD; ensure GPC, cycles, and thickness are consistent; specify supercycle a:b:c only if reported; remove unsubstantiated material property values and composition; keep only traceable device metrics and structure.

completeness.rationale:
Major portions of the extracted data are not traceable to the article and several entries contradict either the text or the schema. The paper only reports: IGZO deposited by ALD as a 10 nm channel; gate insulator 5 nm Al2O3 (or 7 nm HfO2/7 nm Al2O3 in variants); 8 in thermally oxidized p+ Si substrate; device architecture; optional anneal in air at 350 °C for 30 min; and device metrics (μ_FE = 18.3 cm2/V·s, V_TH = 1.1 V, SS = 67.8 mV/dec). It does not specify ALD method (thermal vs plasma), reactor make, precursors/co-reactants, carrier/purge gases, temperature, pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC, supercycle design/ratios, optical constants, resistivity, carrier density, composition ratios, roughness, density, uniformity, or conformality.

Key issues:
- Non-traceable or fabricated values: precursors (“In–Ga bimetallic precursor”, DEZn), co-reactant O3, carrier/purging gases (Ar/N2), reactor manufacturer (ASM), deposition temperature (200 °C), pressure (0.1 mmHg), dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), optical properties, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity, conformality, roughness, film density, composition (XPS-based atomic ratio 1.0:2.8:5.4), on/off ratio, safety/reproducibility. None are reported in the article.
- IGZO ALD supercycle missing/incorrect: schema expects supercycle details for multicomponent IGZO (subcycles for In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO and their a:b:c counts). Extraction provides only a single “InGaZnO” subcycle and sequence, which is not consistent with IGZO ALD practice and not supported by the text.
- Inconsistency: GPC × cycles does not match film thickness (0.1 Å × 100 = 1 nm vs reported 10 nm), indicating internal inconsistency.
- Schema violations: plasmaPower is set to null (type mismatch; the field should be omitted if not used); several required fields are populated with invented values rather than traceable data, undermining schema-guided correctness.
- Partial positives: device metrics μ_FE, V_TH, and SS match the article; device structure text roughly aligns (back-gate IGZO channel 10 nm; Al2O3 GI 5 nm). However, overall the process description is incomplete and largely non-factual relative to the article.

To improve: restrict entries to values explicitly reported (film thickness 10 nm; substrate; device structure; device metrics). Remove or leave out fields not supported by the article. Add missing, article-backed items relevant to the schema such as: IGZO supercycle design (a:b:c) and subcycle sequence (if provided), actual precursors/co-reactant, deposition temperature/pressure, dosing and purge times, flows, and composition/optical/electrical film properties if reported. Also include annealing (350 °C, 30 min, air) if schema permits post-deposition conditions.
